# File Answer

## Goal
Promote a valuable answer, comparison, analysis, or connection — produced during a query or session — into a permanent wiki page in the {{config.project.name}} wiki. Good answers compound back into the knowledge base; they do not disappear into chat history.

## Core Principle
This is the loop that makes the wiki compound from queries as well as from sources. A comparison the user asked for, an analysis you ran, a connection you noticed — these are knowledge artifacts every bit as real as an ingested source. Filed correctly, they become part of the wiki's permanent reasoning.

There is no separate "questions" directory. An answer becomes whichever existing page type best fits its shape:

| Answer shape | Filed to | Page template |
|---|---|---|
| Side-by-side analysis of 2+ subjects | `wiki/comparisons/` | `comparison-table.md` |
| Synthesis, framework, or named pattern | `wiki/concepts/` | `concept-page.md` |
| New named subject (person, org, tool, etc.) discovered through the answer | `wiki/entities/` | `entity-page.md` |

This skill is invoked automatically by `query-wiki` (in autonomous mode) or as a follow-up offer (in deliberate / batch modes). It can also be invoked directly when reviewing a transcript or chat session for material worth preserving.

<workflow>

<step n="1" goal="Identify the answer worth filing">
  <action>If invoked from `query-wiki`, the answer payload is already in hand — proceed to step 2</action>
  <action>If invoked directly, ask the user which answer or session segment to file. Read the relevant chat or transcript</action>
  <action>Decide whether this answer is worth filing. The bar: it drew on at least 2 wiki pages, produced novel synthesis (not just a lookup), and is likely to be useful again. If it fails the bar, say so and stop — do not file every answer.</action>
</step>

<step n="2" goal="Classify the answer's shape">
  <action>Determine which page type fits best:</action>
  <action>- **Comparison**: the answer compares 2+ subjects across attributes. File to `wiki/comparisons/` using `comparison-table.md` template.</action>
  <action>- **Concept**: the answer is a named synthesis, framework, principle, or pattern that does not yet have a page. File to `wiki/concepts/` using `concept-page.md` template.</action>
  <action>- **Entity**: the answer introduced a named subject (person, org, tool, place, product) not yet in the wiki. File to `wiki/entities/` using `entity-page.md` template.</action>
  <action>If the answer is a hybrid (e.g., a comparison that also introduces a new concept), file the primary artifact and create stubs with cross-references for the secondary one</action>
  <action>If the answer extends an existing page rather than warranting a new one, update the existing page instead and treat this as a page-update operation, not a page-creation operation. Note that in the log.</action>
</step>

<step n="3" goal="Pick a slug and verify uniqueness">
  <action>Choose a kebab-case slug that is descriptive and unambiguous (e.g., `transformer-vs-rnn-tradeoffs`, `compounding-knowledge-pattern`)</action>
  <action>Check `wiki/index.md` and the target directory for collisions</action>
  <check if="a page with this slug already exists">
    <action>If it's the same subject, update that page instead of creating a new one — treat this as a page-update operation</action>
    <action>If it's a different subject with a similar name, pick a more specific slug to disambiguate</action>
  </check>
</step>

<step n="4" goal="Create the filed page">
  <action>Use the appropriate template from `.forge/templates/`</action>
{{#if config.wiki.frontmatter}}
  <action>Set frontmatter:</action>
  <action>- `type`: comparison | concept | entity (matches directory)</action>
  <action>- `title`: human-readable</action>
  <action>- `tags`: derived from the originating question and contributing pages</action>
  <action>- `first_mentioned`: today's date</action>
  <action>- `source_count`: number of distinct wiki pages that contributed (this is a wiki-derived page, so its "sources" are the contributing pages, not raw sources)</action>
  <action>- `confidence`: high if all contributing pages were high-confidence and not disputed; medium otherwise; disputed if any contributing claim is itself disputed</action>
  <action>- `status: current`, `supersedes: []`, `superseded_by: null`, `last_verified` = today</action>
{{/if}}
  <action>Write the body using the template's structure. Include the originating question or prompt verbatim in a "Question" or "Origin" subsection so future readers know where this page came from.</action>
  <action>Cite every claim by linking to the wiki page(s) that contributed using {{config.wiki.cross_ref_style}} style — do NOT introduce outside knowledge. The page must be re-derivable from its citations.</action>
  <action>If contributing pages have `confidence: disputed`, surface that nuance here — do not flatten</action>
</step>

<step n="5" goal="Cross-link bidirectionally">
  <action>For each contributing wiki page, add a {{config.wiki.cross_ref_style}} link back to this new page in an appropriate section (Related Concepts, Related Comparisons, etc.) so the new page is discoverable from its sources</action>
  <action>If this answer revealed a contradiction between contributing pages, flag it on the contributing pages with a WARNING callout and `confidence: disputed`, and link to this new page as the analysis of the conflict</action>
</step>

<step n="6" goal="Update index">
  <action>Add the new page to `wiki/index.md` under the correct category, with a one-line description</action>
{{#if (includes config.workflows.tools "qmd")}}
  <action>Run `qmd update` to refresh the search index with the new page</action>
{{/if}}
</step>

<step n="7" goal="Log the filing">
  <action>Append to `wiki/log.md`:</action>
  <action>Format: `## [ISO-timestamp] file-answer | {page title}`</action>
  <action>Include: page path, page type, contributing pages (list), originating question, source_count</action>
{{#if (eq config.workflows.ingestion_style "autonomous")}}
  <action>Prefix with `[AUTO]` if this was triggered by autonomous query compounding</action>
{{/if}}
</step>

<step n="8" goal="Report">
  <action>Tell the user the page was filed, where, and which pages it was derived from</action>
  <action>If contradictions were flagged on contributing pages during step 5, mention them and suggest `adversarial-review` on those claims if the debate agent is enabled</action>
  <action>The wiki is now richer than before this query — the answer has compounded back into the knowledge base instead of disappearing</action>
</step>

</workflow>
